                                         JOHANNESBURG - Two boys have been hospitalised after being hit by lightning in Potchefstroom in the North West. It's understood the incident happened outside their primary school on Thursday afternoon One boy is in a serious condition, while the other sustained moderate injuries. ER24's Russel Meiring said: “Both boys had sustained large burn wounds. Paramedics treated the boys and provided the seriously injured with pain-relief medication before they were transported to nearby hospitals for further treatment.”